Head of Department Structural (Offshore)
02 May 2014 05:09 PM - UAE
.Head of Department Structural (Offshore)Oil and Gas - EPCUAEPermanent
Updated May 2, 2014
The Head of Department- Structural (Offshore) will lead and supervise a team of discipline specialist Engineers and Lead Engineers across a variety of offshore projects. Responsibilities:• You will manage multiple high value complex offshore projects mainly around fixed platform structures. The projects will be varied, large in scale and you will have a large scale and level of managerial and project responsibility at any one time.• Covers all types of activities for all disciplines including conception, FEED, detailed design and EPC projects.• Control staff performance, management of resources and allocation to projects, whilst monitoring progress on each project.• Initiate and maintain QSHE policies• Ensure technical assurance of projects• Identify and qualify new vendors and new subcontractors Who we're looking for The successful candidate will be a strong man manager and leader, capable of managing a large team of engineers across diverse offshore engineering projects within the oil and gas industry.Key requirements for this position are:-• A degree in Engineering discipline• Must have 15 years experience of offshore structural design for the oil and gas industry• Must have a strong technical background and knowledge of offshore structural design• Able to manage people and lead teams on projects• Strong track record of project delivery of offshore structural projects within oil and gasAbout our client Global Oil & Gas EPC business based in UAE.What's on offer Competitive monthly salary (basic, housing and transport) + Schooling, Bonus, Flights, MedicalConta (more...)
